==English==
===Noun===
'''disappointment''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''disappointments''')

#(''uncountable'') The emotion felt when a strongly held [[expectation]] is not met.
#:''Choking back his disappointment after his own team's splendid wins against Liverpool and Aston Villa, he said: "I've got to be humble and say we were beaten by a very good side."'' &mdash; ''Today'', News Group Newspapers Ltd, 1992
#(''countable'') A circumstance in which a strongly held expectation is not met.
#:''As the disappointments crowded in &mdash; the economy, Rhodesia, strife within the trade-union movement &mdash; [[w:Harold Wilson|Wilson]] tried the expedient of a semi-formal inner Cabinet, or Parliamentary Committee, as he misleadingly liked to call it.'' &mdash; ''Cabinet'', Hennessy, Peter, Basil Blackwell Ltd, 1990

